#X text 59 38 The number of output channels in [del.out~] is the maximum of the number of input channels of [de.in~] and the number of input channels in [del.out~]. If both are of the same size \, each input signal sets the delay time of a correspondent delay channel. In case the numbers mismatch \, the smaller wraps around until reaching the number of the bigger one. So a single input value simply sets the delay time of all channels. Using more signal inputs than the available number of channels is useful for implementing a multitap delay., f 82;
